learning_outcomes.en:
A student who defends a Bachelor's thesis:
1. identifies, with assistance of a supervisor, a problem suitable for research in a particular field of theology;
2. finds, with assistance of a supervisor, literature on the main treatments of the respective problem and principal source texts, if necessary;
3. presents, based on an independent analysis, a reasoned overview of the approaches to the problem, solution attempts and research methods; 
4. writes the text in accordance with the principles of drawing up research papers;
5. is able to present and defend his/her research results in an oral presentation in a concise manner.
